The placeholder replace `currentUrlStr.replace(/^\/\//, 'http://')` - after the `http://` prepend replace, when would the result start with `//`? The prepend replace uses a lookahead `(?!(?:\w+:)?\/\/)` - it won't prepend if already starts with `//`. So if input starts with `//`, the prepend does nothing, and then the placeholder converts `//` to `http://`.

